# shadcn/ui First Rule

- Use shadcn/ui as the default source of base UI primitives.
- Before creating a custom primitive, check whether shadcn/ui already provides the component.
- Prefer extending or composing shadcn/ui primitives over replacing them.
- Shared reusable primitives belong in `shared/ui`.
- Business-specific compositions belong in `entities`, `features`, or `widgets`.
- Do not create parallel internal design-system primitives that duplicate shadcn/ui.
- During migration, replace old primitives with shadcn/ui incrementally while preserving behavior and accessibility.